Citation.sAbstract: The present work focuses on the application of a deep eutectic solvent (DES) to the separation of liquid mixtures. Experimental activity coefficients at infinite dilution  13 of 23 organic solutes in tetrapropylammonium bromide + 1,6-hexanediol DES were measured by gas-liquid chromatography (GLC) at four temperatures ranging from (313.15 to 343.15) K and atmospheric pressure. The hydrogen bond acceptor-to-hydrogen bond donour molar ratio was 1:2. The effect of molecular structure on the values of  13 was also examined.
